# Loan Approval Insight Visualization
Power BI & Excel Data Analysis Project
## Project Overview
This project provides a data-driven analysis of loan approval decisions using Power BI and Excel.
It explores how key financial factors such as credit score, income, employment status, and loan amount influence whether a loan is approved or rejected.
The dashboard is interactive, visually intuitive, and business-focused, making it useful for:
Financial institutions
Credit analysts
Business decision-makers
Data analysis learners
## Objectives
✔ Analyze loan approval vs rejection rates
✔ Identify key factors influencing loan approval
✔ Visualize patterns and trends using charts and slicers
✔ Build an interactive dashboard for decision support
## Dataset Description
The dataset contains the following key fields:
Applicant ID
Loan Status (Approved / Rejected)
Annual Income
Credit Score
Loan Amount
Employment Duration
Total Credit
Data was cleaned and transformed before visualization.
## Dashboard Features
. Total Loans
. Approved vs Rejected Loans
. Average Credit Score
. Total Loan Amount
. Annual Income Analysis
. Interactive Slicers
. Clear KPIs and Charts
## Tools & Technologies
Microsoft Power BI
Microsoft Excel
Data Cleaning & Transformation
Pivot Tables & Charts
Interactive Slicers
## Key Insights
Applicants with higher credit scores have a significantly higher approval rate
Stable income and longer employment duration improve approval chances
Large loan amounts combined with low income increase rejection risk
## How to Use This Project
Download or clone the repository
Open the Power BI (.pbix) or Excel file
Use the slicers to filter by loan status and financial attributes
Explore trends and insights interactively
